Subject: Ethmia festiva 
To: Charlotte
Content:
Ethmia festiva is a moth in the Ethmiidae family. It is found from south-eastern Mexico and Guatemala to northern Colombia. The length of the forewings is 8.3-10 mm. The ground color of the forewings is white with distinct brownish black lines which reflect bluish. The ground color of the hindwings is whitish, becoming brownish apically. Adults are on wing from late March to May (in Yucatan and Panama), in July (Oaxaca and Nicaragua) and in July and October (in Colombia).[1]
